snippet.title: Rihanna - Same Old Love (Lyrics) "take away your things and go" [Tiktok Song]

Lyrics:

[Intro: Charli XCX]
Oh, oh, oh

[Verse 1: Rihanna]
Take away your things and go
Can't take back what you said, oh no
I've heard it all before, at least a million times
I'm not one to forget, you know

[Pre-Chorus 1: Rihanna]
I don't believe, I don't believe it
You left in peace, left me in pieces
Too hard to breathe
I'm on my knees right now

[Chorus: Rihanna]
I'm so sick of that same old love, that shit it tears me up
I’m so sick of that same old love, my body's had enough
Oh-oh-oh, that same old love
Oh-oh-oh that same old love
I’m so sick of that same old love, feels like I've blown apart
I’m so sick of that same old love, the kind that breaks your heart
Oh-oh-oh, that same old love
Oh-oh-oh, that same old love

[Verse 2: Rihanna]
I'm not spending any time, wasting tonight on you
I know, I've heard it all
So don't you try and change your mind
So I won't be changing too, you know

[Pre-Chorus 2: Rihanna]
I don't believe, I don't believe it
You left in peace, left me in pieces
Too hard to breathe, I'm on my knees right now, oh

[Chorus: Rihanna]
I'm so sick of that same old love, that shit, it tears me up
I’m so sick of that same old love, my body's had enough
Oh-oh-oh, that same old love
Oh-oh-oh, that same old love
I’m so sick of that same old love, feels like I've blown apart
I’m so sick of that same old love, the kind that breaks your heart
Oh-oh-oh, that same old love
Oh-oh-oh, that same old love

[Bridge: Rihanna]
I'm so sick of that, so sick of that love (hey!)
I'm so sick of that, so sick of that love
I'm so sick of that, so sick of that love (hey!)
I'm so sick of that, so sick of that love

[Chorus: Rihanna]
I'm so sick of that same old love, that shit, it tears me up
I’m so sick of that same old love, my body's had enough
Oh-oh-oh, that same old love
Oh-oh-oh, that same old love
I’m so sick of that same old love, feels like I've blown apart
I’m so sick of that same old love, the kind that breaks your heart
Oh-oh-oh, that same old love
Oh-oh-oh, that same old love
